Users can now save any document directly to DMS (Document Management System
)
like iManage directly from Microsoft applications like Word, Excel etc. They need to upgrade to Power PDF 5.1 to get this feature.

if the same file "NamedUsersList.txt" in place is now recreated edited in notepad on windows machine, it is saved with UTF-8 encoding;
This resolved the issue as we can see 4 activations and the license count has adjusted as expected with new installations.
For further information on how to configure the license server, please reference the power PDF network installation guide included with your version of Power PDF you are deploying

- select any *.pdf file in Windows Explorer;
- right-click on it and select Open with\Choose another app;
select Power PDF, mark "Always use this app to open *.pdf files" checkbox and click "Ok".
To invoke this for automation when a user logs in, the following command can be run in batch file;
{PATH}\DefaultViewer.exe /SetDefault
This presents the wizard to have them interactively set the default so we are compliant to Microsoft's design going forward in windows in how an application requires the user interaction to set the default, not programmatically.
